The paper presents an interactive system that visually summarizes feature attribution over time for different feature values in decision-making with temporal sequences using Deep Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN). This work involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which suggests that cs.HC is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the interpretability of RNN models, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL. Finally, the paper uses a large dataset of electronic health records, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CY.
